The paper deals with state estimation for intelligent applications such as robot navigation and autonomous driving, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes an approach for calibrating temporal offset between visual and inertial measurements, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and optimization (cs.LG). The approach is also applicable to feature-based optimization frameworks, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper demonstrates the high accuracy of the proposed approach, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI).
